@node "Loader" "Loader"
@{b}@{u}YCrCb Loader@{ub}@{uu}

The YCrCb Loader loads files saved by the GVP TBCPlus timebase corrector
(in the @{"YCrCb format" link "Format"}) into ImageFX. The YCrCb Loader is not limited in any
way if you choose not to @{"register" link "Registration"}.

@endnode

@node "Distribution" "Distribution"
@{b}@{u}Distribution@{ub}@{uu}

YCrCb should be distributed at no charge to the end user. It may be
included on CDs such as Fish and Aminet. The YCrCb executable and
documentation is shareware, however payment is not required for its use.

@{"Registering" link "Registration"} YCrCb ensures small (local) programmers continue to support the
Amiga platform with quality shareware software.

For ANY commercial application using the YCrCb loader, contact the @{"author" link "Author"}
for further information concerning distribution.

@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation"
@{b}@{u}Installation@{ub}@{uu}

This package should contain:
  YCrCb = The loader to copy into ImageFX:Modules/Loaders.
  YCrCb.030 = A 68030 optimized version of the loader.
  YCrCb.guide = The document you are reading now.

@endnode

@node "Format" "YCrCb Format"
@{b}@{u}YCrCb File Format@{ub}@{uu}

The TBCPlus' native file format is YCrCb 601-1. This is a digital
television transmission color space (YIQ and YUV are the analogue form for
NTSC and PAL). It separates luminance from chrominance (lightness from
color) and is useful in compression and image processing applications. The
format is device dependent, like RGB, but it is calibrated (ie The colour
white is determined by a standards committee). Y is the Luminance
component, Cr and Cb the chrominance components red and blue respectivley.
(Some parts taken from comp.graphics FAQ.)

I have reverse engineered the file format (many thanks to my high school
algebra and calculus teachers :-) and have been able to load successfully
most files I have @{"saved" link "Bugs"}. It is possible that a file would exist that the
loader will not interpret correctly. I know that this loader is not as fast
as the TBCPlus software is, but I am really only guessing as to how exactly
it works. I'm just not a very good guesser I suppose ;-)

Please contact me if you have a file that doesn't load properly so that I
can try and fix the problem.

@endnode

